# Pulumi.yaml (project) AND Pulumi.<stack>.yaml (per-stack config) are both
# committed: this module is driven from CI (the preview/apply workflows), which
# need the stack config (repoOwner + the policy toggles) at runtime. repo_config
# uses only NON-secret config; Pulumi stores any secret config encrypted, so the
# stack config is safe to commit. (The negations below override any parent
# .gitignore that ignores Pulumi.*.yaml, e.g. a copybara repo's.)
!Pulumi.yaml
!Pulumi.*.yaml

# Compiled Pulumi program binary left behind by a manual `go build .` (named
# after the module's last path element).
/repo_config
/pulumi
